FBIS3-60515 "jptep002___94043" JPRS-TEP-94-002 Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Epidemiology 13 January 1994 LATIN AMERICA CUBA Porcine Cholera Detected in Havana, Pinar del Rio FL2611231293 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1255 GMT 26 Nov 93 FL2611231293 Havana Radio Rebelde Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Text] Porcine cholera, a viral pig disease not observed in Cuba since 1974, has been detected in Pinar del Rio and Havana Provinces, while Havana City, Matanzas, and Isle of Youth have been declared threatened areas. The transportation of pigs within and between provinces is not recommended.
